About - Spencer Capital



































Spencer Capital



FIRM OVERVIEW





Founded by Dr. Ken Shubin Stein in 2000, Spencer Capital Management is a global investment advisor based in New York City. Drawing upon Dr. Shubin Stein’s dual backgrounds in the fields of medicine and financial services, the firm takes a concentrated, value oriented and systematic approach to investing in the global equity markets.





The firm’s sharp focus on processes is one of its defining aspects and has allowed it to develop a specialized investing approach that recognizes and reduces biases that can distort decision making, drive unconscious behaviors and ultimately sub-optimal investing decisions.






LEADERSHIP
Kenneth Shubin Stein, MD, CFA – Founder & Portfolio Manager











Dr. Ken Shubin Stein is the Founder and Portfolio Manager of Spencer Capital Management, LLC and the Chairman of Spencer Capital Holdings, LTD. He is a graduate of the Albert Einstein College of Medicine where he completed a 5-year medical and research program with a focus on molecular genetics. He graduated with a B.A. degree from Columbia College with dual concentrations in Premedical Studies and Political Science. Ken holds the CFA designation and is an adjunct professor at the Columbia University Graduate School of Business. Ken is also Chairman Emeritus of the Manhattan Chapter of YPO and Founder and Chairman of Crutches 4 Kids, a not-for-profit organization dedicated to providing crutches to children in need around the world.





GIVING BACK




Aligned with Spencer Capital Management’s scientific investing model is the firm’s commitment to philanthropy. The firm takes the same methodological and process driven investing approach to helping others.
Dr. Shubin Stein’s foundation, Crutches4Kids, collects and distributes crutches to children in need, globally. The organization’s ability to effectuate change by providing a real solution to a tangible problem is what makes it such a unique platform.
